HEADWORD: Straitly
<hw>Strait"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a strait manner;
narrowly; strictly; rigorously.</def> <rj><au>Mark i. 43.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Closely; intimately.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straitness</ent>⟦br⟧
